# IAM Roles and Policies

This document outlines the IAM roles and permissions used in the Serverless Social Media Analytics project.

---

## 1. üîê Lambda Execution Role

**Role Name:** `lambda-kinesis-s3-execution-role`

**Purpose:**  
Allows the Lambda function to:
- Read from Kinesis Data Streams
- Write to Amazon S3
- Write logs to CloudWatch

**Required Policy Permissions:**

```json
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "kinesis:GetRecords",
        "kinesis:GetShardIterator",
        "kinesis:DescribeStream",
        "kinesis:ListStreams"
      ],
      "Resource": "*"
    },
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "s3:PutObject",
        "s3:PutObjectAcl"
      ],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::your-output-bucket-name/*"
    },
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "logs:CreateLogGroup",
        "logs:CreateLogStream",
        "logs:PutLogEvents"
      ],
      "Resource": "*"
    }
  ]
}

2. Quicksight Access


{
  "Effect": "Allow",
  "Action": [
    "s3:GetObject",
    "s3:ListBucket"
  ],
  "Resource": [
    "arn:aws:s3:::your-output-bucket-name",
    "arn:aws:s3:::your-output-bucket-name/*"
  ]
}
